OL,5,CChancellor
OL,7,FThere's a growing sense he intends to
OL,8,Ffollow through on his election pledges.
OL,10,FAll this matters because when the UK
OL,11,Fgovernment's borrowing costs go up,
OL,12,Fmortgage rates also tend to rise.
OL,14,FAnd higher bond yields, if sustained,
OL,15,Fcould be a huge problem for a
OL,16,Fchancellor who has promised to balance
OL,17,Fthe books.
